        <h3>The Future of Grails</h2>
   		<p>We have reached an inflection point in Java web development. The last one we met on this scale was the rise of Spring, as it aggressively displaced most of J2EE. A consensus formed soon after Spring was paired with Struts,
   		that this, finally, was the way to do Java web development. Take some MVC implementation, attach to a Spring IoC container, or Guice if you want to be radical....</p>
