   <h3>Groovy and Grails thoughts</h3>
   	<p>I've been slowly banging away at a small Grails app on the train to and from work, to teach myself Groovy the language and Grails the web framework. I already had a good familiarity with Java, Spring and Hibernate so it is mostly
   	 a case of learning what Groovy and Grails add on top of those. I've still got a long way to go, but I thought it worth jotting down some thoughts in case....</p>
   		<a href="http://alwaysthecritic.typepad.com/atc/2010/08/groovy-and-grails-thoughts.html" title="Read more about Enterprise Web Development ">Read more</a>
       </li>
